---
layout: base.njk
title: "Blog — Harry Wellbelove"
description: "Writing on security engineering, homelab infrastructure, detection engineering, and things learned the hard way."
permalink: /blog/
---

<main>
<div class="wrap page-content">
  <section class="section fade-in">
    <div class="page-label">Blog</div>
    {% if collections.posts.length %}
    <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
      Blog
    </h1>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;">
      {% for post in collections.posts | reverse %}
      <li style="margin-bottom:24px;">
        <a href="{{ post.url }}" style="font-size:18px;font-weight:600;">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
        <time style="display:block;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:4px;">{{ post.date | dateFormat }}</time>
        {% if post.data.description %}
        <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6;margin-top:6px;">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
        {% endif %}
      </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
    {% else %}
    <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-bottom:24px;">
      Nothing here <em class="accent">yet.</em>
    </h1>
    <p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:32px;">
      Nothing published yet, but posts are coming — security engineering,
      the homelab that keeps finding new ways to break, detection rules
      I've written, and lessons learned the hard way.
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/">← Back home</a>
    {% endif %}
  </section>
</div>
</main>
